Frank A. COLONELL, Appellant, v. Benjamin S. GOODMAN et al. No. 9642. Circuit Court of Appeals. Third Circuit. Argued June 10, 1948. Decided July 2, 1948. Writ of Certiorari Denied Nov. 22, 1948. See 69 S.Ct. 166. John J. Gain, of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant. Charles E. Kenworthey and Bernard G. Segal, both of Philadelphia, Pa., for Parkway Oil Co., appellee.

Before BIGGS, GOODRICH, and KALODNER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the court below will be affirmed upon the careful opinion of Judge Kirkpatrick, 78 F.Supp. 845.
